I apologize for the horrible naming and horrible placement, but I'm drawing a huge blank on terminology, so please rename and move this for me.

The issue is explained easily with this gif.
![2019-06-11 15 58 14](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23037821/59312585-89514880-8c62-11e9-83af-b81155efd5ef.gif)



Thanks for the feedback! If your issue is related to the Flutter framework itself,
please open an issue at
[github.com/flutter/flutter](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/new).

## Steps to Reproduce
type an if statement like so:
`if(true) return false;`
insert an open curly brace and press enter and the closing bracket will place itself after the following word regardless of what's actually there.
if(true)**{|** return false;
turns to 
```dart
 if(true){
      return
    } false;
```
_Please tell us what you were doing and what went wrong_
Minding my own business when next thing I knew, this happened!

Thanks for the feedback! The work to address this would likely happen in the Dart plugin for IntelliJ

I can repro something similar to your above screenshot in Dart code. When I do the same in Java, IntelliJ does put the matching `}` in a location you'd expect (the curly braces are balanced appropriately). 

cc @jwren @alexander-doroshko

My pleasure. Someone please move it to the appropriate place. It's hard to
figure out and place issues in the correct place. I'm just proud of myself
for getting this up here

I can't reproduce either. @devoncarew any tips on how you reproduced the issue?

I was able to repro via:

```
      if (true) /*caret*/return;
```

However, I did see correct behavior in other situations:

```
      if (!serviceManager.hasConnection) /*caret*/toast('Device connection lost.');
```

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!

title: Code reformatted incorrectly when using ifs with no brackets
